<b> Headers/Cookies: </b>
- Headers represent the meta-data associated with the API request and response. In layman terms, we were sending Additional details to API to process our request.
- Example : Authorization details
- Just like adding authorization layer to authenticate the request. meaning that when we're requesting something the API will check the cookie if it has the login cookie.
- Similary in header were giving the type of the response whether it is html/xml/json that data we're adding in header.


<b> End Point Request URL can be constructed as below : </b>
>Base URL/resource/(Query/Path)Parameters


